The paper deals with complexity parameters for the Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP), which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper proposes a new complexity parameter called joinwidth, which is based on the arrangement of basic operations on relations (joins, projections, and pruning) required to solve the instance. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DB (Databases).
